title: Recent Talks Roundup
---

Since last posting, I've been lucky enough to travel to many fascinating places - arranging events, giving invited talks, and participating in panel discussions. Some details and pictures are gathered below: a heartfelt thanks to _all_ of the organisers who have made this possible!

April 2026 has already involved events at [Robosoft 2026](https://www.robosoft2026.org/), Kanazawa, and Tokyo, where I:

- Gave an invited talk and joined a panel discussion on Monolithic Soft Systems in Robotics.
- Gave an invited talk on non-contact object manipulation in a workshop "_Exploiting Fluids and Embodied Intelligence in Soft Robotics._"
- Helped to organise a new workshop: "_Electrical Impedance Tomography-Based Tactile Sensing: Bridging Soft Robotics and Artificial Touch_", where I also joined the closing panel discussion.

Additionally:

- At the end of February I visited the [Max Planck Institute for Intelligent Systems](https://is.mpg.de/en) in Stuttgart, to speak in their 2026 Scientific Symposium.

- In August I gave an invited talk on my work at the [International Flexible Electronics Technology Conference (IFETC)](https://ieee-ifetc.org/) in Vancouver, where it was great to connect with an entirely new community! I also gave a keynote talk at the STEM WP Summer Internship Conference, held at Cambridge's [Institute for Manufacturing](https://www.ifm.eng.cam.ac.uk/).

- In June I gave an invited talk at the [Hamlyn Symposium on Medical Robotics](https://www.hamlynsymposium.org/), held at the beautiful Royal Geographical Society in London.

- November came with the chance to return to EPFL's [CREATE Lab](https://www.epfl.ch/labs/create/) in snowy Switzerland, for a set of meetings and collaborations with [our ARIA project's](https://aria.org.uk/opportunity-spaces/smarter-robot-bodies/robot-dexterity/meet-the-creators/?cardId=scalable-tactile-sensing-dexterous-multi-tool-use) collaborators.

Next month I'll be at [ICRA 2026](https://2026.ieee-icra.org/) in Vienna as one of the workshop organisers bringing together the community in large-area tactile sensing. Find out more [here](https://large-area-tactile-sensing.github.io/).

